issues.description: The template's Stock.findStockIngredient method signature (String, boolean) does not match the one described in the problem statement and used in the solution (String). Students will attempt to call stock.findStockIngredient(name) as specified, but the template only offers stock.findStockIngredient(name, caseSensitive), causing compilation errors.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the template to include a findStockIngredient(String) method matching the problem specification and solution—either by overloading the existing method or by providing the correct single-parameter signature.
